## Installation

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone {{repositoryUrl}}
cd {{projectName}}
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
{{packageManager}} install
```

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### 3. Setup Tauri

```bash
# Install Tauri CLI
{{packageManager}} install -D @tauri-apps/cli

# Verify Tauri setup
{{packageManager}} run tauri info
```

**Common Issues**:
- **Missing system dependencies**: See [Tauri Prerequisites](https://tauri.app/v1/guides/getting-started/prerequisites)
- **Rust not found**: Ensure Rust is in your PATH after installation
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
### 3. Setup AWS

```bash
# Install AWS CDK
npm install -g aws-cdk

# Bootstrap CDK (first time only)
cd infrastructure
cdk bootstrap
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

### 4. Environment Configuration

Create `.env.local` file:

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

Edit `.env.local`:

```bash
# Application
{{#if nextjs-aws}}
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/api
{{/if}}

{{#if tauri}}
# Tauri app identifier
TAURI_APP_ID=com.{{projectName}}.app
{{/if}}

{{#if nextjs-aws}}
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/{{projectName}}

# Authentication
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-here
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

# AWS (for production)
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
{{/if}}

# TODO: Add environment variables
```

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
### 5. Database Setup

```bash
# Start database (Docker)
docker-compose up -d postgres

# Run migrations
{{packageManager}} run db:migrate

# Seed data (optional)
{{packageManager}} run db:seed
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

