## Building for Production

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### Desktop App

```bash
# Build production app
{{packageManager}} run tauri build

# Output locations:
# macOS: src-tauri/target/release/bundle/dmg/
# Windows: src-tauri/target/release/bundle/msi/
# Linux: src-tauri/target/release/bundle/deb/
#        src-tauri/target/release/bundle/appimage/
```

**Build Configuration**:
- Edit `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`
- Set app name, version, identifier
- Configure bundle settings
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
### Web App

```bash
# Build Next.js app
{{packageManager}} run build

# Test production build locally
{{packageManager}} run start
```

### Deploy to AWS

```bash
cd infrastructure

# Deploy all stacks
cdk deploy --all

# Or deploy specific stack
cdk deploy FrontendStack
cdk deploy ApiStack
```

**Deployment outputs**:
- Frontend URL: CloudFront distribution URL
- API URL: API Gateway endpoint
- Database endpoint: RDS instance
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if tauri-aws}} -->
### Hybrid Deployment

**Desktop App**:
```bash
{{packageManager}} run tauri build
```

**Cloud Backend**:
```bash
cd infrastructure
cdk deploy --all
```

Update desktop app with cloud API URL:
```bash
# Edit .env.production
VITE_API_URL=https://api.production.example.com
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

